-----BEGIN CERTIFICATE-----
... paste the Origin Certificate block from Cloudflare here ...
... it will be ~25-30 lines of base64-looking text ...
-----END CERTIFICATE-----

NOTE: This file (origin.crt.example) is just a layout reference and
must NOT be the file nginx loads. Rename it / create a new file at
deploy/ssl/origin.crt with the real cert pasted between the BEGIN
and END markers, no extra blank lines before or after.

If Cloudflare gave you a chain (multiple BEGIN/END blocks), keep them
in the order Cloudflare returned (leaf first, then intermediates) —
nginx reads top-to-bottom and presents them to the client in that
order.
